---
id: org.dxos.plugin.blogger
name: BloggerPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A Composer plugin for authoring blog posts with agent assistance. An author
organises work into **Publications** (a named collection with shared base
agent instructions) that contain **Posts**. Each Post has a planning
**outline** and a single commentable markdown **body** document, plus a
`status` (draft | published) tracking whether it has been synced to a
publisher.

The plugin also defines a provider-agnostic **publisher** capability contract
(`PublisherService`) and a bidirectional sync operation that consumes it.
`plugin-typefully` is the first implementation, authenticating via a
`plugin-connector` `Connection`. A publisher connection is associated with a
Publication via a `ConnectorAuthAnnotation` (mirroring plugin-studio's
Artifact) — the connector plugin offers "Connect <publisher>" until a matching
`Connection` exists in the space.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |

### Existing types used by this plugin

| Type                 | Source                      | Notes                                                                 |
| -------------------- | --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `Text.Text`          | `@dxos/schema`              | Backs `Publication.instructions` and `Post.outline`.                  |
| `Markdown.Document`  | `@dxos/plugin-markdown`     | Backs `Post.content` (the commentable body).                          |
| `Connection`         | `@dxos/plugin-connector`    | Provider-neutral credential handle passed to every `PublisherService` call. |

## Types

```mdl
type Post
  desc: >
    A blog post: a planning outline plus a single commentable markdown body
    document. `status` tracks whether the post has been synced to a publisher;
    the remote id (once synced) is stored as a foreign key on the post's meta,
    keyed by the publisher's `source`. `description` is shown on PostCard.
  typename: org.dxos.type.blogger.post
  fields:
    name?: string
    description?: string            # shown on PostCard
    status: draft | published       # lifecycle; defaults to draft
    outline: Ref<Text.Text>         # planning outline (markdown-formatted)
    content: Ref<Markdown.Document> # the commentable body
  annotations:
    icon: ph--article--regular
    hue: amber
    label: [name]
```

```mdl
type Publication
  desc: >
    A named collection of Posts carrying shared base instructions for the
    assistant agent. Carries a ConnectorAuthAnnotation resolving the registered
    PublisherService's connectorId(s), so plugin-connector offers "Connect"
    until a matching Connection exists.
  typename: org.dxos.type.blogger.publication
  fields:
    name?: string
    instructions: Ref<Text.Text>    # base agent instructions (markdown-formatted)
    posts?: Ref<Post>[]
  annotations:
    icon: ph--books--regular
    hue: amber
    label: [name]
    connectorAuth: resolvePublicationConnectorIds   # from registered PublisherService.connectorId
```

```mdl
type PublisherDraft
  desc: >
    Provider-neutral post DTO exchanged across the PublisherService boundary
    (the provider's own vocabulary — Typefully calls posts "drafts"). A plain
    Effect Schema.Struct — NOT an ECHO object.
  fields:
    id: string
    text: string
    title?: string
    status?: string
    scheduledAt?: string
    url?: string
```

```mdl
type PublisherDraftInput
  desc: Input shape for PublisherService.createDraft / updateDraft.
  fields:
    text: string
    title?: string
    scheduledAt?: string
```

## Components

```mdl
component PublicationArticle
  desc: >
    Article surface for a Publication (AppSurface.object(Article,
    Publication)). A toolbar toggle swaps between two view modes: `gallery`
    (default) — a Masonry grid of PostCard tiles, one per `subject.posts` —
    and `instructions` — the Publication's shared instructions document,
    embedded via the markdown article Surface. The toolbar also carries a
    `+ Post` action, a `Sync` action (invokes op:SyncPosts; enabled once a
    matching Connection exists), the plugin-connector "Connect" action (merged
    from the app graph via the Publication's ConnectorAuthAnnotation), and an
    overflow (⋮) menu whose Delete opens a confirmation AlertDialog.
  props:
    role: string
    attendableId: string
    subject: Publication
  state:
    mode: gallery | instructions
    confirmDeleteOpen: boolean
  actions:
    toggleView()
    addPost()
    sync()
    openPost(post: Post)
    delete()                        # via confirmation dialog
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ [toggle-view][+ Post][Sync][Connect]      [⋮] │
    ├──────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ gallery: Masonry of PostCards                  │
    │   -or-                                         │
    │ instructions: markdown Surface                 │
    └──────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component PostArticle
  desc: >
    Article surface for a Post (AppSurface.object(Article, Post)). The outline
    form (name + inline outline) renders on top and the single body
    Markdown.Document renders below via the markdown article Surface, wrapped in
    an AttendableContainer (the body editor is rendered outside the Deck plank
    wrapper, so it supplies its own attendable id — a graph-node path,
    qualifyId(<post node id>, doc.id) — so graph.actions resolves the in-editor
    comment action). `status` and the publisher link are managed by the
    publication-level op:SyncPosts, not here.
  props:
    role: string
    attendableId: string
    subject: Post
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ post form (name + outline)                │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ body (markdown Surface)                   │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component PostCard
  desc: >
    Summary tile for a Post, rendered as a Masonry Tile in
    PublicationArticle's gallery view. Reactive to the passed Post via
    useObject. Shows the post's status (draft | published).
  props:
    post: Post
    onClick?: () => void
  layout: |
    ┌────────────────────────┐
    │ [icon]  title           │
    │ description excerpt     │
    │ [status-icon]  status   │
    └────────────────────────┘
```

## Services

```mdl
service PublisherService
  desc: >
    Provider-agnostic publishing backend contract. Implemented by a provider
    plugin (e.g. plugin-typefully) and contributed under
    BloggerCapabilities.PublisherService; op:SyncPosts resolves one contribution
    via Capability.getAll. Identity fields: `id` (capability id), `label`
    (display name), `source` (matches AccessToken.source, e.g.
    "typefully.com"), `connectorId` (matches Connection.connectorId / the
    Connector registry entry id). Every method takes a Ref<Connection> — the
    provider-neutral credential handle; token resolution stays entirely in the
    implementing plugin. The provider's vocabulary ("draft") is kept at this
    boundary; the blogger domain uses "Post".
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    listDrafts(connection: Ref<Connection>) → PublisherDraft[]
    getDraft(connection: Ref<Connection>, id: string) → PublisherDraft
    createDraft(connection: Ref<Connection>, input: PublisherDraftInput) → PublisherDraft
    updateDraft(connection: Ref<Connection>, id: string, input: PublisherDraftInput) → PublisherDraft
    deleteDraft(connection: Ref<Connection>, id: string) → void
  errors:
    PublisherError: sync failed against the remote backend
    MissingCredentialError: the service's credentials (e.g. Connection's access token) are missing
```

## Operations

```mdl
op AddPublication
  desc: >
    Creates a new Publication (with an empty instructions document and no
    posts) and files it under `target`.
  input:
    name?: string
    target: Database | Collection
  output: Ref<Publication>
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op AddPost
  desc: >
    Creates a new Post (an outline plus a single empty body document, status =
    draft) and appends it to `publication.posts`, also filing it under
    `target`.
  input:
    publication: Ref<Publication>
    name?: string
    target: Database | Collection
  output: Ref<Post>
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op SyncPosts
  desc: >
    Bidirectionally reconciles a Publication's posts with an external publisher,
    keyed by the remote id stored as a foreign key on each post's meta (source =
    the publisher's `source`). Local body content is the source of truth for
    posts already linked to a still-present remote draft.
      - post linked to a still-present remote draft → push the local body (updateDraft);
      - post linked to a remote draft that was deleted → clear the key, status = draft;
      - post with no link → create the remote draft, stamp the returned id, status = published;
      - remote draft not linked to any post → create a new local Post (stamped, status = published).
  input:
    publication: Ref<Publication>
    connection: Ref<Connection>
    publisherId?: string            # selects a contributed service by id; defaults to the first available
  output: Ref<Publication>
  errors:
    PublisherError: no publisher configured, or a remote call failed
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [PublisherService]
  note: >
    Resolves via Capability.getAll(BloggerCapabilities.PublisherService),
    preferring publisherId when given.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Publications Section

  req F-1.1: A "Publications" section is contributed under each space's content group (mirroring plugin-studio's Studio section), listing that space's Publication objects as branch nodes.
  req F-1.2: "+ Publication" on the Publications section invokes op:AddPublication targeting that space's database.
  req F-1.3: Each Publication node expands to its Post children, with a "+ Post" action invoking op:AddPost.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Publication Authoring

  req F-2.1: component:PublicationArticle defaults to the gallery view: a Masonry grid of component:PostCard, one per Post.
  req F-2.2: Toggling the toolbar view swaps to the instructions view — the Publication's shared instructions document, rendered via the markdown article Surface.
  req F-2.3: "+ Post" in the toolbar invokes op:AddPost against the open Publication.
  req F-2.4: Delete lives in an overflow (⋮) menu and opens a confirmation AlertDialog before invoking SpaceOperation.RemoveObjects.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Post Authoring

  req F-3.1: op:AddPost creates a Post with an outline document, a single empty body document, and status = draft.
  req F-3.2: component:PostArticle shows the outline form on top and the single body document below (markdown Surface).
  req F-3.3: component:PostCard shows the post's status (draft | published).
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Comments on the Post body

  req F-4.1: Post.content is a Markdown.Document, so comments anchor to it automatically via the AnchoredTo relation (plugin-comments). The postComments graph extension contributes the comments companion (anchored to the body doc) and a hidden, addressable node for the body doc so the in-editor comment toolbar action resolves.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Agent Instructions per Publication

  req F-5.1: `Publication.instructions` is a Text.Text the author edits directly, carrying the base instructions the assistant agent reads for that Publication. Agent consumption of these instructions is Phase 2 and is NOT built here.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Publisher Connection and Bidirectional Sync

  req F-6.1: type:Publication carries a ConnectorAuthAnnotation resolving the registered service:PublisherService connectorId(s); plugin-connector contributes a "Connect <publisher>" action (surfaced in component:PublicationArticle's toolbar) until a Connection for that connectorId exists in the space.
  req F-6.2: op:SyncPosts pushes each unlinked local Post to the publisher (createDraft), stamping the returned id as a foreign key and setting status = published.
  req F-6.3: op:SyncPosts updates the remote copy of each linked Post whose remote draft still exists (local body wins), and reverts a linked Post whose remote draft was deleted to status = draft (clearing the foreign key).
  req F-6.4: op:SyncPosts pulls each remote draft not linked to any local Post into a new published Post (body via getDraft when listDrafts omits it), stamped with the remote id.
  req F-6.5: The Sync action in component:PublicationArticle is disabled until a service:PublisherService is contributed AND a Connection whose access-token source matches it exists in the same space.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: AddPublication persists an empty Publication
  given: a database db
  when: op:AddPublication invoked with { name: "My Blog", target: db }
  then:
    - Publication.name === "My Blog"; Publication.posts === []
    - Publication.instructions resolves to an empty Text.Text
    - Publication is queryable from db via Filter.type(Publication)
```

```mdl
test T-2: AddPost creates outline + body and defaults to draft
  given: a persisted Publication and a target Collection
  when: op:AddPost invoked with { publication, name: "Hello World", target }
  then:
    - publication.posts gains a ref resolving to the new Post
    - Post.status === "draft"
    - Post.outline resolves to an empty Text.Text
    - Post.content resolves to a Markdown.Document
    - Post is filed under `target` (Collection.objects)
```

```mdl
test T-3: SyncPosts pushes an unlinked local post
  given: a Publication with one unlinked Post, a stub PublisherService
  when: op:SyncPosts invoked (service.listDrafts returns [])
  then:
    - service.createDraft called
    - the Post's foreign key for service.source === the returned remote id
    - Post.status === "published"
```

```mdl
test T-4: SyncPosts updates a linked local post (local wins)
  given: a Post linked to remote id "x1"; service.listDrafts returns ["x1"]
  when: op:SyncPosts invoked
  then:
    - service.updateDraft called with id "x1" (service.createDraft NOT called)
    - the Post's foreign key unchanged ("x1")
```

```mdl
test T-5: SyncPosts reverts a linked post whose remote was deleted
  given: a published Post linked to remote id "gone"; service.listDrafts returns []
  when: op:SyncPosts invoked
  then:
    - no create/update/delete calls
    - the Post's foreign keys for service.source === []
    - Post.status === "draft"
```

```mdl
test T-6: SyncPosts pulls an unlinked remote draft into a new published post
  given: a Publication with no posts; service.listDrafts returns ["x2"]
  when: op:SyncPosts invoked
  then:
    - a new Post is appended to publication.posts with content === the remote body
    - the new Post's foreign key for service.source === "x2"; status === "published"
```

```mdl
test T-7: SyncPosts falls back to getDraft when listDrafts omits body text
  given: a Publication with no posts; service.listDrafts returns ["x2"] with empty text
  when: op:SyncPosts invoked
  then:
    - service.getDraft called once for "x2"
    - the pulled Post's body === getDraft("x2").text
```

## Design Notes

- **Navtree hub (per space).** The Publications section is contributed per
  space under the `content` group (`AppNodeMatcher.whenNavTreeGroup`), mirroring
  plugin-studio's Studio section — so each space shows its own Publications, and
  the section is always present as the create hub. A custom Publication node
  type scopes the "+ Post" action so it never attaches to Publication objects
  listed under the space's Database section.
- **Publisher connection.** A publisher connection is associated with a
  Publication via the `ConnectorAuthAnnotation` (mirroring plugin-studio's
  Artifact): plugin-connector offers "Connect <publisher>" until a Connection
  for the publisher's connectorId exists. component:PublicationArticle resolves
  the first contributed service:PublisherService and the first Connection in the
  space whose linked AccessToken's `source` matches it — there is no
  publisher/connection picker UI yet. `op:SyncPosts` takes an explicit
  `connection` ref, so a picker is additive.
- **Naming.** The blogger domain uses "Post"; the provider adapter
  (service:PublisherService) keeps the provider's "draft" vocabulary at its
  boundary (Typefully has no "posts").
- Phase 2 (agent skills/operations for ideate/draft/publish) is out of scope
  for this spec.

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap        # name[?]: TypeExpr  (# inline comment)
    literals?: UnionList     # a | b | c
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self              # feat blocks may contain feat blocks
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap            # external inputs (immutable inside component)
    state?: FieldMap            # internal reactive state
    slots?: FieldMap            # named ReactNode injection points
    actions?: ActionMap         # methods the component exposes or handles
    emits?: EventMap            # events the component raises to its parent
    layout?: CodeBlock          # ASCII sketch of visual structure (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap            # named input parameters
    output?: TypeExpr           # return type
    errors?: ErrorMap           # name: Prose  (when this error occurs)
    effects?: EffectList        # echo:read | echo:write | http | fs | ...
    requires?: ServiceList      # injected service dependencies
    note?: Prose                # implementation guidance (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap                 # name(params) → ReturnType
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
